{{current}} The '''26 November 2008 Mumbai attacks''' were twelve attacks of terror happening at the same time across [[Mumbai]], [[India]], around 80 people have been killed and 900 have been injured.<ref name="mumbaiattack-toi">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Terrorists_strike_Mumbai_80_dead_many_hurt/articleshow/3761410.cms|title=Terror attacks in Mumbai; 80 dead, over 900 injured|publisher=[[Times of India]]|date=November 27, 2008|accessdate=2008-11-26}}</ref> A group called [[Deccan Mujahideen]] which was not known before, has said it was responsible for the attacks.<ref name="mumbaiattack-toi"/> It is possible that they are a part of the [[Indian Mujahideen]]<ref name=im>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.digitaltoday.in/index.php?option=com_content&issueid=71&task=view&id=15328&sectionid=4&Itemid=1|title=Indian Mujahideen threatens to target Mumbai|publisher=India Today}}</ref>
